to the editor i appreciate the feelings of christy ferer unforgotten soldiers op ed oct 25 about ground zero and about the special treatment given to celebrities it is indeed a burial ground however i have heard many times that one can not appreciate the scope of the devastation from a television picture americans need to understand that devastation to steel their resolve in this crisis many of us feel that this horror has not changed our lives much there are the nagging voices of doubt as well telling us that the united states deserved this that others are right to hate us that we should n't go to war or increase security measures that may limit some of our accustomed liberties i have a feeling that such voices would be refuted and silenced if we could all experience ground zero allen s thorpe castle dale utah oct 25 2001

